GulfTalent.com
Supply Chain Manager
Morgan McKinley
Dubai, UAE
Posted on: 5 May 2014
THE ROLE
Expand all
Our client is one of the world’s largest FMCG companies with regional operations headquartered in Dubai responsible for the GCC region.
Due to the growth of the organization they are seeking a Supply Chain Manager to support the market demand.
The Supply Chain Manager will be responsible for the end-to-end supply chain operations and provide significant input into the development and execution of the operations strategy and driving operational efficiencies to support aggressive growth strategies. This role will involve a high-level of cross-functional interaction between inbound supply, customers, logistics and sales.
REQUIREMENTS
Essential:
- Bachelor’s Degree and at least 5 years relevant experience in Supply Chain operations in FMCG organization
- Experience of procurement and strategic sourcing in the Middle East & Africa
- Excellent Negotiating skills
Skills:
- Strategic thinker
- Team leadership
- Demand planning
- Budgeting
- SAP knowledge
ABOUT THE COMPANY
In November 2010, GCC specialist recruiter, iQ selection came together with global professional recruitment consultancy Morgan McKinley, under the name Morgan McKinley.
With 24 offices globally, Morgan McKinley connects specialist talent with leading employers across multiple industries and disciplines. We work very closely with international corporates, top investment banks and local SMEs to provide those looking for their next career move with the best job opportunities.
From our Dubai office, we provide specialist recruitment expertise spanning Financial Services & Finance; Sales, Marketing & Support; and Technical sectors throughout the GCC region, with dedicated consultants delivering focused sector and local knowledge. In addition, we are fully committed to promoting the government’s Emiratisation policy.
